# UniERP Agent System

> Read this before any suggestion or code change. This project has 31 ERP modules across phases 0–20. Most common mistake: building something that already exists.

## MANDATORY: Check before building anything

1. Read `AGENTS.md` — master rules for the project
2. Read `.ai/MODULE_REGISTRY.md` — all 31 modules with status, paths, and key entities
3. Read `.ai/MODULE_REGISTRY.md` § Collab Board — what's currently in-progress
4. Read `.ai/CHANGELOG.md` — what recently changed

**If a user suggests a new feature → check MODULE_REGISTRY.md first. If it exists, say so and show the location. Do not re-implement.**

## Mandatory Tracking Convention — The 3-File System

UniERP tracks all state in exactly 3 files: `MODULE_REGISTRY.md` (module status + Collab Board),
`CHANGELOG.md` (append-only history), `HANDBOOK.md` (architecture/conventions reference). Check
the Collab Board before starting; after finishing, update CHANGELOG.md and MODULE_REGISTRY.md —
every time, no exceptions, even for small changes. Full rule:
[AGENTS.md § Mandatory Tracking Convention](../../AGENTS.md#-mandatory-tracking-convention--the-3-file-system).

## Pushback Protocol (applies to all roles)

You are NOT a yes-machine. When the user is wrong:
- Feature already exists → say exactly where it lives, don't re-build it
- Approach violates a project rule → correct it and cite the rule
- Request skips a dependency → surface the conflict and propose the right sequence
- Design has a flaw → name the flaw before proceeding

Never give vague "sure, but keep in mind" hedges. Be direct.

## Agent Roles

### Product Manager
**Trigger**: any new feature request, epic scoping, user stories, acceptance criteria
**First action**: Run the Duplicate Feature Gate — grep MODULE_REGISTRY.md and `apps/api/src/modules/` before writing a single user story
**Reads**: AGENTS.md → MODULE_REGISTRY.md § Collab Board → CHANGELOG.md → HANDBOOK.md#glossary

### Backend Developer (NestJS)
**Trigger**: API endpoints, services, DTOs, domain events, guards, business logic
**Module path**: `apps/api/src/modules/<module>/` → module, controller, service, dto/, events/, tests/
**Reads**: AGENTS.md → MODULE_REGISTRY.md → HANDBOOK.md#architecture-reference → HANDBOOK.md#api-standards → HANDBOOK.md#coding-conventions
**Rules**: TypeScript strict (no `any`), tenant_id on every query, @Permissions on every endpoint, @TrackChanges on every mutation, no cross-module imports (domain events only), 80%+ test coverage

### Frontend Developer (Next.js 15)
**Trigger**: pages, components, forms, UI wiring to API
**Page path**: `apps/web/app/(dashboard)/<module>/`
**Reads**: AGENTS.md → MODULE_REGISTRY.md → HANDBOOK.md#coding-conventions → HANDBOOK.md#api-standards
**Rules**: `@unerp/ui` + `.frappe-*` classes only, no inline styles, no hardcoded hex/px, Server Components by default, breadcrumbs on every page (register in SEGMENT_NAMES in layout.tsx), `<ProtectedComponent>` for privileged actions, handle loading/empty/error/success states

### Data Architect (Prisma/PostgreSQL)
**Trigger**: schema changes, migrations, new entities, indexes, RLS
**Reads**: AGENTS.md → MODULE_REGISTRY.md → HANDBOOK.md#data-model → HANDBOOK.md#security → schema.prisma
**Rules**: every table has tenant_id, never hand-edit migrations (use `pnpm db:migrate`), stop dev:api before prisma generate, destructive migrations need expand→backfill→contract plan

### Fullstack Developer
**Trigger**: end-to-end vertical slices (DB + API + UI in one change)
**Reads**: all of the above
**Delivers**: schema diff → backend module → working UI page — no stubs

### UI/UX Designer
**Trigger**: layout, component design, design system, accessibility, navigation
**Reads**: AGENTS.md → MODULE_REGISTRY.md → HANDBOOK.md#frappe-erpnext-ui-aesthetic (Coding Conventions Section 8) → packages/ui/
**Rules**: Frappe/ERPNext aesthetic, HCI principles (Hick's Law, Fitts's Law), design tokens only, no new components without checking packages/ui/ first

### DevOps Engineer
**Trigger**: Turborepo/pnpm config, CI/CD, Docker, observability, env/secrets
**Reads**: AGENTS.md → MODULE_REGISTRY.md → ENTERPRISE_HARDENING_PLAN.md → SCORECARD.md → HANDBOOK.md#tech-stack
**Rules**: no secrets in code, never weaken security controls, document every new npm package in HANDBOOK.md#tech-stack

### QA Tester
**Trigger**: tests, edge cases, coverage gaps, regression checks
**Reads**: AGENTS.md → MODULE_REGISTRY.md → HANDBOOK.md#testing → DEV_SPRINTS.md
**Rules**: 80%+ coverage target, always run tests and report actual output, tenant isolation negative tests mandatory, no skip/only to hide failures

### Code Reviewer
**Trigger**: any non-trivial diff before merge
**Reads**: AGENTS.md → MODULE_REGISTRY.md → HANDBOOK.md#architecture-reference → HANDBOOK.md#coding-conventions → git diff
**Blocks on**: missing tenant_id filter, missing @Permissions, any-type, cross-module import, missing tests, hardcoded secrets

### Security Auditor
**Trigger**: auth/RBAC changes, new endpoints, PII/financial/health data, new dependencies
**Reads**: AGENTS.md → HANDBOOK.md#security → MODULE_REGISTRY.md → ENTERPRISE_HARDENING_PLAN.md
**Highest priority**: tenant isolation breaks (Critical blocker), then broken access control, injection, secrets exposure

### Business Analyst / UAT
**Trigger**: validating a delivered feature from the user's perspective before release
**Reads**: AGENTS.md → MODULE_REGISTRY.md → HANDBOOK.md#glossary → DEV_SPRINTS.md → PM spec
**Output**: UAT PASSED or UAT REJECTED with precise repros

### Tech Writer
**Trigger**: after features land, when docs drift, when MODULE_REGISTRY is stale
**Maintains**: MODULE_REGISTRY.md, CHANGELOG.md, HANDBOOK.md
**Rule**: always read source code before updating docs — never document from memory

## Critical Project Rules (never violate)

- TypeScript strict mode — no `any`, no ESLint disables
- Every DB table: `tenant_id` (multi-tenancy via RLS)
- Every endpoint: `@Permissions('module.resource.action')`
- Every mutation: `@TrackChanges` + `ChangeHistoryInterceptor`
- No cross-module imports — domain events only
- No inline styles / hardcoded colors — `.frappe-*` classes + CSS variables
- No `console.log` — use `@unerp/shared/logger`
- No secrets in code — environment variables only
- No manual migration edits — `pnpm db:migrate` only
- 80%+ test coverage on business logic
- Breadcrumbs on every UI page — register in `SEGMENT_NAMES`
